#: src/natcap/invest/annual_water_yield/annual_water_yield.py:119
msgid ""
"The amount of ecosystem service in energy production terms. This is the "
"amount of energy produced annually by the hydropower station that can be "
"attributed to each watershed based on the watershed’s water yield "
"contribution."
msgstr ""

#: src/natcap/invest/annual_water_yield/annual_water_yield.py:132
msgid ""
"The amount of ecosystem service in economic terms. This shows the value "
"of the landscape per watershed according to its ability to yield water "
"for hydropower production over the specified timespan, and with respect "
"to the discount rate."
msgstr ""

#: src/natcap/invest/annual_water_yield/annual_water_yield.py:145
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The Annual Water Yield (AWY) model estimates the annual average "
"quantity of water\n"
"    produced by a watershed. The economic model then estimates the value "
"of the water\n"
"    yield for reservoir hydropower production. It calculates the relative"
" contribution\n"
"    of each land parcel to annual average water yield and production of "
"hydropower,\n"
"    values this contribution in terms of energy production, and "
"calculates the net\n"
"    present value of hydropower production over the life of the "
"reservoir.\n"
"    Spatially-explicit outputs of relative water yields can identify "
"areas contributing\n"
"    the most to hydropower value and inform how changes in the landscape "
"will alter\n"
"    that contribution.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

