#: src/natcap/invest/carbon/carbon.py:20
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The InVEST Carbon Storage and Sequestration model uses maps of land "
"use\n"
"    along with stocks in four carbon pools (aboveground biomass,\n"
"    belowground biomass, soil, and dead organic matter) to estimate the\n"
"    amount of carbon stored in a landscape at baseline or the amount of\n"
"    carbon sequestered over time. Optionally, the market or social value "
"of\n"
"    sequestered carbon, its annual rate of change, and a discount rate "
"can\n"
"    be used to estimate the value of this ecosystem service to society.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

