#: src/natcap/invest/seasonal_water_yield/seasonal_water_yield.py:31
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The Seasonal Water Yield (SWY) model estimates the amount of water "
"produced\n"
"    by a watershed, arriving in streams over the course of a year. The "
"primary\n"
"    outputs of the model are quickflow, local recharge, and baseflow. "
"Quickflow\n"
"    represents the amount of precipitation that runs off of the land "
"directly,\n"
"    during and soon after a rain event, and local recharge represents the"
" amount\n"
"    of rainfall that infiltrates into soil, minus what is evaporated or "
"used by\n"
"    vegetation. Baseflow is the amount of precipitation that enters "
"streams more\n"
"    gradually through sub-surface flow, including during the dry season. "
"The model\n"
"    is based on inputs of topography (DEM), soils, land cover and "
"management,\n"
"    rainfall, and vegetation water demand.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

