#: src/natcap/invest/urban_nature_access/urban_nature_access.py:39
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The InVEST Urban Nature Access model allows for examination of access"
" to\n"
"    the recreational, social, psychological, and physical health benefits"
" of\n"
"    nature. Assessing nature-based recreation and its health benefits "
"first\n"
"    requires an understanding of both the \"supply\" of urban nature and\n"
"    \"demand\" for urban nature. The supply is determined by the type, "
"size,\n"
"    proximity, and quality of urban nature, while the demand depends on\n"
"    people's preferences or local policy requirements/urban planning\n"
"    standards. The InVEST Urban Nature Access model provides a measure of"
"\n"
"    both supply and demand for urban nature, as well as the supply-demand"
"\n"
"    balance, which quantifies the extent to which supply meets demand at\n"
"    the individual, administrative, and city levels.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#: src/natcap/invest/urban_nature_access/urban_nature_access.py:55
msgid "Urban Nature Access"
msgstr "Acceso urbano a la naturaleza"

